-- Kenya Reinsurance 1st-half profit up 6 pct on new business
-- By James Macharia
-- Thu Aug 14, 2014 10:38AM EDT
-- None



NAIROBI, Aug 14 (Reuters) - Kenya Reinsurance Corp <KNRE.NR> reported a 6 percent rise in first-half pretax profit to 1.7 billion shillings ($19.4 million) on Thursday as revenue increased from its businesses in Kenya and other African markets.

Gross written premiums climbed 23 percent to 4.9 billion shillings in the first six months of the year. Investment income rose to 1.3 billion shillings from 1.2 billion shillings.